 		      PresentCompleteKindMSCNotify }
@@ -338,6 +339,53 @@ The name of this extension is "Present"
 	defined by the extension, but is expected to be on the order
 	of milliseconds or less.
 
+	PresentCapabilitySyncobj means that the target device supports
+	explicit synchronization using timeline DRM synchronization
+	objects. See the PresentPixmapSynced request for details.
+
+┌───
+    PresentPixmapSynced
+	window: WINDOW
+	pixmap: PIXMAP
+	serial: CARD32
+	valid-area: REGION or None
+	update-area: REGION or None
+	x-off, y-off: INT16
+	target-crtc: CRTC or None
+	wait-fence: FENCE
+	idle-fence: FENCE
+	syncobj: SYNCOBJ or None
+	acquire-point: CARD64
+	release-point: CARD64
+	options: SETofPRESENTOPTION
+	target-msc: CARD64
+	divisor: CARD64
+	remainder: CARD64
+	notifies: LISTofPRESENTNOTIFY
+└───
+	Errors: Window, Pixmap, Match, Value
+
+	Identical to the PresentPixmap request, with the addition of an
+	optional syncobj argument, along with acquire and release points,
+	to be used for explicit GPU synchronization. If the target device
+	supports PresentCapabilitySyncobj and 'syncobj' is not None,
+	'acquire-point' and 'release-point' are assumed to correspond to
+	timeline points for the given DRM synchronization object.
+
+	GPU access to the image by the server will be gated by the
+	'acquire-point'.  The client must ensure that the fence for this
+	timeline point has been submitted before issuing the request.
+
+	Once the 'release-point' has been signaled, the client may assume
+	that no further GPU access to the image by the server will occur.
+	This fence is guaranteed to have been submitted by the time the
+	PresentIdleNotify event is received.
+
+	If 'syncobj' is not None and does not refer to a previously
+	imported syncobj, either 'acquire-point' or 'release-point' is
+	zero, or 'acquire-point' is greater than or equal to
+	'release-point', a Value error is returned.
+
 
